parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inoperative Seat Belts due to Retractor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become jammed or inoperable, leaving the driver or passenger unsecured, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt pulls out and locks
making it impossible to put on
the seat belt becomes jammed and will not function
the seat belt will not come out of the retractor
the seat belt retractor fails to lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle, combined with the loss of brake function, can lead to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the brakes become inoperable
the vehicle is unable to stop
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the brake line can cause a loss of brake function, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The brake line leaks or corrodes
causing a loss of brake fluid
the brakes become inoperable
and the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake caliper can cause a loss of brake function, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The brake caliper falls off
the brake pedal grabs or pulsates
the vehicle experiences a loss of braking ability
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose line can cause a loss of brake function, leading to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS system locks up
the vehicle experiences a loss of braking ability
and the driver may experience a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, resulting in a total loss of the vehicle, and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire
